## Context

User-observed pain on a live `uv run maiba scan tests/fixtures/ArchiveCCS.ris`
(2026-04-28): the CLI prints nothing until the entire scan finishes. The
user has no signal that work is happening or how far along it is.

The 223-record dry-run takes ~2–4 minutes against live OpenAlex/Crossref;
without progress feedback this feels broken. (Cache work to address the
runtime itself is split into ticket 0009.)

## Actions

No new dependency. Per record, write one character to `sys.stderr`
(flushed), followed by a newline at the end.

| Char | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `.`  | Skipped — record had no gaps |
| `0`  | Not fixed — resolver returned None or confidence below `apply_threshold` |
| `*`  | Fully fixed — every detected gap filled by the resolver |
| `+`  | Partially fixed — at least one gap filled, at least one still open |

1. In `src/maiba/pipeline.py` `run()`, classify each record's outcome
   into one of the four states above and call `_emit_progress(char)`
   right after the per-record decision.
2. `_emit_progress` writes to `sys.stderr` (flushed). Suppress when
   `sys.stderr` is not a TTY so logs/CI stay clean:
   `if not sys.stderr.isatty(): return`.
3. After the loop ends, write `"\n"` to stderr so the next CLI line
   starts clean.
4. Add `--quiet` to `maiba scan`. When set, suppress glyphs even on a TTY.

### Edge cases
- Empty input → no glyphs, no trailing newline (the loop just doesn't run).
- An exception mid-loop → the partial glyph stream stays on screen; the
  finally clause emits the trailing newline so the shell prompt isn't
  jammed against the last glyph.

## Test (TDD red step)

```python
# tests/test_progress.py
import sys
from pathlib import Path

import respx
from httpx import Response

from maiba.config import load_config
from maiba.pipeline import run


@respx.mock
def test_progress_glyph_per_record_on_tty(monkeypatch, tmp_path, capsys):
    monkeypatch.setattr(sys.stderr, "isatty", lambda: True)
    # Default-deny network: no resolver hits; every gapped record gets `0`.
    respx.get(url__startswith="https://api.openalex.org").mock(
        return_value=Response(200, json={"meta": {"count": 0}, "results": []})
    )
    respx.get(url__startswith="https://api.crossref.org").mock(
        return_value=Response(
            200,
            json={"status": "ok", "message": {"items": [], "total-results": 0}},
        )
    )
    cfg = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
    run(input=Path("tests/fixtures/good.ris"), output=tmp_path / "out.ris",
        cfg=cfg, apply=False)
    err = capsys.readouterr().err
    glyphs = err.rstrip("\n")
    assert len(glyphs) == 3
    assert all(c in ".0*+" for c in glyphs)
    assert err.endswith("\n")


def test_progress_suppressed_when_stderr_not_tty(monkeypatch, tmp_path, capsys):
    monkeypatch.setattr(sys.stderr, "isatty", lambda: False)
    cfg = load_config("config/maiba.yaml")
    # Empty fixture → loop doesn't fire either way; verifies no crash on non-tty.
    run(input=Path("tests/fixtures/empty.ris"), output=tmp_path / "out.ris",
        cfg=cfg, apply=False)
    assert capsys.readouterr().err == ""
```

A small unit test on the classification helper would also be nice
(`_classify(gaps_before, fields_changed_count) -> char`) — bare logic,
no I/O.

## Exit criteria

- `make test` green; new tests above pass.
- `uv run maiba scan tests/fixtures/good.ris` (TTY) prints `.0*+`-class
  glyphs on stderr, one per record, with trailing newline.
- `uv run maiba scan tests/fixtures/good.ris --quiet` produces no glyphs
  even on a TTY.
- `make lint` green.
- The four glyphs are module-level constants in `pipeline.py`; not config-tunable.
